HEADWORD: Acetabuliferous
<hw>Ac`e*tab`u*lif"er*ous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acetablum</ets> a little cup + <ets>-ferous</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Furnished with fleshy cups for adhering to bodies, as cuttlefish,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

